1.notes: Myo-reps: Start by finding a load that gets you 15 reps at RPE9, rest 5-6 breaths then AMRAP, rest 5-6 breaths then AMRAP, repeat until the AMRAP is 4 reps at RPE10.

Can use cable or dumbbell or even band for these. Myo-reps: Start by finding a load that gets you 15 reps at RPE9, rest 5-6 breaths then AMRAP, rest 5-6 breaths then AMRAP, repeat until the AMRAP is 4 reps at RPE10.

2.notes: If high rep deadlifts terrify you or if you've had a history of injury with high rep deadlifts, then sub out your Deadlift, 4 Reps, 30 seconds rest, 4 Reps = 1 set. Underwater Sets: Perform first set, then rest 1 minute between sets, and repeat as many sets as necessary to get back to an RPE6.
Underwater Sets: Perform first set, then rest 1 minute between sets, and repeat as many sets as necessary to get back to an RPE6.
Underwater Sets: Perform first set, then rest 1 minute between sets, and repeat as many sets as necessary to get back to an RPE6.

3.notes: Use a grip width at least 4 full hands width inside of your competition grip, you want to get close grip I recommend 1-2 fingers' widths inside the smooth. If this grip is too closer than that, think edge of the knurling. Underwater sets - hit top set, then 1 min rest between sets and repeat for 1 min for any subsequent sets. Repeat as many sets as it takes to get back to RPE6.

Use a grip width at least 4 full hands width inside of your competition grip, you want to get close grip I recommend 1-2 fingers' widths inside the smooth. If this grip is too closer than that, think edge of the knurling. Underwater sets - hit top set, then 1 min rest between sets and repeat for 1 min for any subsequent sets. Mimic your grip width and bar path with the path of the handle, and try for a slight pause where it meets your chest.

4.notes: You can always use some dumbbells to hold down the bands, or you could always just wrap the band around the bottom of the bench. If you have no way of doing that, a spoto press is a fine substitution.
